{{wikipediapar|Cabal}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From French ''[[cabale]]'' from Medieval Latin ''[[cabala]]'' from which [[Kabbalah]] is also derived. It is likely that the mystical often secretive nature of Kabbalah led to formation of the word cabal.

===Pronunciation===
'''IPA''': kɐbaɫ

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A usually [[secret]] exclusive [[organization]] of [[individual]]s gathered for a [[nefarious]] purpose.
#: ''The '''cabal''' is plotting to take over the world.''
# A secret [[plot]].
#:''The '''cabal''' to destroy the building was foiled by federal agents.''
# An identifiable group within the tradition of [[w:Discordianism|Discordianism]].
#:''Some episkoposes have a one-man '''cabal'''.  Some work together.  Some never do explain.'' - from the ''[[w:Principia Discordia|Principia Discordia]]''

